                  <summary>Letter to Panakestor: the writer was imprisoned, asks Panakestor for help, and would like him to write to Zoilos on his behalf; he takes an oath by King Ptolemy, Arsinoe and the daimon which was the guardian of Panakestor</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers with 14 lines; on the back, along the fibers, the address</note>
                     <note type="general">Line beginnings are missing and fibers are badly torn</note>
                     <note type="general">The hand is practiced but uneven and with letters retraced: a personal hand</note>
                     <note type="general">There is a wide bottom margin of 3.5 cm</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
